comments: LLS shows Parker (WAS) places his hands on Sabonis' (IND) back during rebounding, but he does not extend his hands into Sabonis' body.  The reaction from Sabonis is not consistent with the contact from Parker.
Bogdanovic (IND) maintains legal guarding position and makes incidental contact with Ariza (WAS) that does not affect his SQBR.
Satoransky (WAS) is already in Bogdanovic's (IND) path when contact occurs and he does not deliver contact.
LLS shows Bryant (WAS) does not establish a legal screening position in Matthews' (IND) path and the contact occurs to his side.
Parker (WAS) makes contact to Sabonis' (IND) arm that affects his SQBR in transition.
[Observable in enhanced video] Beal (WAS) moves his pivot foot heel to toe to create distance.
[Detectable with stop watch] Ariza (WAS) does not inbound the ball within five seconds.
Sabonis (IND) places his hand momentarily on Bryant's (WAS) hip during the inbound.
As the defenders switch during the inbound, Bryant (WAS) delivers some contact as he sets the screen on Collison (IND).
Sabonis (IND) makes contact to Beal (WAS) on his drive to the basket and shot attempt.
MOB and LAR show Satoransky (WAS) moves laterally into Sabonis' (IND) path and makes contact to Sabonis' arm that causes him to lose control of the ball.
Beal (WAS) places a hand/arm to the front of Collison (IND) and this allows Beal to make contact with the ball.
[Observable in enhanced video] Satoransky (WAS) slides his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
Bryant (WAS) rolls to the rim and does not affect Collison's (IND) ability to defend the play.
LAR shows Young (IND) legally contests Parker's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Satoransky (WAS) makes marginal contact with Young (IND) that does not affect his ability to control the ball.
RAR shows Collison (IND) establishes his right foot as his pivot foot, and Collison legally lifts his pivot foot to pass.
RAR shows Bogdanovic (IND) and Satoransky (WAS) make incidental contact with one another as they attempt to secure the loose ball.

call_type: Turnover:  Out of Bounds - Bad Pass Turn
comments: After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor (WAS) ball was confirmed.
LAR shows Matthews (IND) legally contests Beal's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
Parker (WAS) commits a take foul on Sabonis (IND).

After Bryant (WAS) has secured the rebound, Parker (WAS) makes contact to Bogdanovic's (IND) head as the two players turn to go down the floor.  Contact to an opponent's head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Bogdanovic (IND) does not affect Parker's (WAS) ability to secure the rebound.
Bogdanovic (IND) legally contests Ariza's (WAS) jump shot attempt.
LAR shows Bogdanovic (IND) makes incidental contact with Bryant (WAS) after Bryant has safely landed following his jump shot attempt.
LLB shows Ariza (WAS) makes contact to Collison's (IND) arm that causes Collison to momentarily lose control of the ball, and he quickly regains possession.
Bryant (WAS) cleanly deflects the ball away from Sabonis (IND).
Sabonis (IND) legally contests Bryant's (WAS) jump shot attempt.

Ariza (WAS) moves laterally into Collison's (IND) path and makes body to body contact with Collison that affects his SQBR.  This contact would allow Ariza to make any contact with the ball, and the contact occurs prior to any potential contact Ariza may make with the ball.
Sabonis (IND) legally contests Satoransky's (WAS) jump shot attempt.  Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Parker (WAS) commits a take foul on Matthews (IND).
